title: Camelback Ridge
text: Camelback Ridge () is a short rock ridge in <a href="Antarctica">Antarctica</a>, with topographic highs of at the ends, located just west of <a href="Pemmican%20Bluff">Pemmican Bluff</a> in the <a href="Jones%20Mountains">Jones Mountains</a>. It was mapped by the <a href="University%20of%20Minnesota">University of Minnesota</a> Jones Mountains Party, 1960–61, who named it for its humped appearance.
